# Advanced Matrix Operations Library in C++

Improved version of a matrix operations project implemented in C++ using object-oriented programming and modular design.

## Improvements Over Previous Version

- Enhanced class design for matrix handling
- Improved memory management strategies
- Better modular structure with clearer separation of responsibilities
- More maintainable and scalable codebase
- Refactored utility functions

## Features

- Custom floating-point matrix class
- Dynamic memory allocation and management
- Modular architecture (`.cpp` + `.h`)
- Utility functions for matrix operations
- Encapsulation and abstraction

## Project Structure

- `practica2.cpp` → Main program
- `CMatFloat.cpp` → Matrix class implementation
- `CMatFloat.h` → Matrix class definition
- `utils.cpp` → Helper functions
- `utils.h` → Utility declarations
- `MemoryManager.h` → Memory management utilities

## Concepts Covered

- Advanced Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
- Class design and encapsulation
- Dynamic memory management
- Modular programming in C++
- Code refactoring and improvement

## Technologies

- C++
- Standard Library
